    "Id": "chassisdef_texihuitl_TEX-R1",
    "Name": "Texihuitl",
    "Details": "The -R1 variant represents exactly what RISC is all about, highly experimental and focused technology while ignoring any conventional customs or practices. A 475 rated engine core using their proprietary ultralight engine technology, almost 27 tons of Micro-Alloyed Ferro-Fibrous Armor, a Radical Heat Sink Kit and a specialized Emergency Coolant System for superheavies - this 'Mech has it all. Even on the weapons department it is impressive, if for a different reason. A total of 90 Heavy MRM tubes with 5 tons of ammunition show the total commitment to the single-mindedness of the design. To be able to squeeze it all into the 'Mech heavy use of Patchwork Materials was also needed.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - HMRM</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.43</color></b>\n\n<br><br><color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
